  __markedentry = {[goshng]},
  abstract = {A number of statistical tests for detecting population growth are
	described. We compared the statistical power of these tests with
	that of others available in the literature. The tests evaluated fall
	into three categories: those tests based on the distribution of the
	mutation frequencies, on the haplotype distribution, and on the mismatch
	distribution. We found that, for an extensive variety of cases, the
	most powerful tests for detecting population growth are Fu's F(S)
	test and the newly developed R(2) test. The behavior of the R(2)
