  number = {3},
  month = {Nov},
  __markedentry = {[goshng]},
  abstract = {Contingency tests of neutrality are performed using mitochondrial
	cytochrome oxidase II (COII) DNA sequences from hominoid primates,
	including humans. An intra-/interspecific haplotype tree is estimated,
	including a statistical assessment of ambiguities in tree topology
	and branch lengths. Four functional mutational categories are considered:
	silent and replacement substitutions in the transmembrane portion
	of the COII molecule, and silent and replacement substitutions in
	the cytosolic portion. Three tree topological mutational categories
	are used: intraspecific tips, intraspecific interiors, and interspecific
	fixed mutations. A full contingency analysis is performed, followed
	by nested contingency analyses. The analyses indicate that replacement
	mutations in the cytosolic portion are deleterious, and replacement
	mutations in the transmembrane portion and silent mutations throughout
